This paper involves the use of machine learning models for spatial and visual connectivity analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the process of training and evaluating different neural networks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on workplace layouts, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of floor plans, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
